HEADWORD: cirio
<hw>cirio</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the candlewood of Mexico and
southwestern California (<spn>Idria columnaris</spn> or <spn>Fouquieria
columnaris</spn>), having tall columnar stems and bearing honey-scented
creamy yellow flowers; -- called also the <altname>boojum
tree</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> boojum tree, <spn>Fouquieria columnaris</spn>,
<spn>Idria columnaris</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cirriped</ent>⟦br⟧
